LNIB GLOCK 30 SUBCOMPACT 2nd generation (also called the "Big Baby" Glock) .45 cal. Trijicon front and rear night sights.1 ten round magazine. No box no papers ZERO issues. Great large caliber concealable pistol. Serial # is ECXxxx. I bought 4 of these Glock 30's in the "gun rush. Just trying to trim down a little. 

It's surprising this statement is necessary but I guess it is……I had this pistol sold recently but the deal fell through at the last minute because the buyer didn't know the law or I was being set up. Regardless, my time was wasted. It’s ok to not know. I’d just suggest educating yourself one way or another before trying to buy a weapon. 
~ If you transact a private party sell across state lines and are caught & convicted- it is a felony. According to the law- private party transactions should only happen inside the state for which you live. Secondly, if you get the buyer to come off the price- it's not always smart to suggest they drive an hour to meet you (that part is OP ED). 

Bottom line is, this is a fantastic weapon. I love the GLOCK 30. In my opinion, in an urban combat situation where concealment, high capacity & functionality is required- there's not a better pistol available at this price point. If you've ever owned a GLOCK, you know they function clean or dirty/ wet or dry and with pretty much any kind of ammo. Also- there's a TON of accessories.
I have a standing offer of $525 from a guy locally that I’ve done business with before. Good luck

for those not familiar, this is a great 30 caliber round, uses standard AR-15 magazines (will come with 2 P-mags) and you can shoot standard or subsonic rounds.  With a silencer and subsonic rounds it is accurate to 300+ yards and as quiet as an air gun.
The .300 whisper round is simply a 5.56 casing with the neck cut off, then sized for a 30 caliber bullet, the round ends up having the same length and size of a 5.56 so you still get the same magazine capacity, and re-loaders can easily make your own ammo out of spent 5.56 brass.

title: For Sale:  Saiga 12 IZ433 Taktika
postcontent:
The Saiga-12 IZSL-433A is a 030-type semi-automatic shotgun professionally converted. It features US made parts, like Molot style pistol grip, Arsenal Nato length buttstock, and Tapco G2 trigger group. This combination of parts make it a more tactical design if compared with the standard IZ-433 Saiga 12. The US parts used in this gun makes it fully 922R compliant. The shotgun is also equipped with a magazine guide (magwell) and an automatic last round bolt hold open device in order to help facilitate easy reloads and insertion of the magazine. It also has a self regulating gas system, which is unique from all other Saiga-12 shotguns. The top cover features a Picatinny rail on top allowing various optical devices to be attached to aid in sighting. The top cover is also hinged to the rear sight block in order to provide the top-mounted Picatinny rail with the ability to hold zero. An adjustable rear notched sight and front sight post are also standard on the shotgun to assist in accurate firing when no optical device is affixed.
Comes with 2 10 round SGM mags, and 2 factory 4 round mags.
Pickup in Athens or will ship to your FFL.
